WEBVTT

00:02.602 --> 00:05.170
[ Wave crashes ]

00:10.443 --> 00:13.445
[ Screeches ]

00:13.447 --> 00:14.546
Adventure Time

00:14.548 --> 00:15.881
Come on, grab your friends

00:15.883 --> 00:18.650
We'll go to
very distant lands

00:18.652 --> 00:21.220
With Finn and Jake
and Susan Strong

00:21.222 --> 00:22.688
And possibly BMO

00:22.690 --> 00:24.890
It's Adventure Time

00:33.967 --> 00:37.736
Candy Child: "Mom! I wanna
play outside with Consuelo!"

00:37.738 --> 00:40.639
"Cool your jets!
It is super dangerous outside.

00:40.641 --> 00:43.308
Little kids have to stay
in the castle."

00:43.310 --> 00:45.344
"But I'm rowdy!"

00:45.346 --> 00:49.882
"Yeah, well, but look --
see what happens?

00:49.884 --> 00:51.817
You want a playdate
with death?

00:51.819 --> 00:53.685
That's why you have to stay
inside!

00:53.687 --> 00:56.922
And 'cause Consuelo's mom
is a pain in the neck."

00:56.924 --> 00:58.857
I --
[ Gasps ]

00:58.859 --> 01:02.995
In the heat of the sun, you burn
like a pink little baby!

01:02.997 --> 01:04.096
Help!

01:04.098 --> 01:06.698
What?
Oh! A scweam!

01:06.700 --> 01:10.436
Help!
Well, now, what seems to be
the trouble?

01:10.438 --> 01:12.438
I saw something
in the water!

01:12.440 --> 01:14.373
And I was like,
"No thanks!"

01:14.375 --> 01:16.008
Out of my way,
muffin man!

01:16.010 --> 01:17.376
How rude.

01:17.378 --> 01:22.214
Well, whatever that little girl
saw will be a mystery forever.

01:25.853 --> 01:30.389
Transport for seeker
XJ-7-7 "Strong" has arrived.

01:30.391 --> 01:33.459
Please verify identity
as "Strong."

01:33.461 --> 01:37.229
Oh! Trust me,
I'm strong indeed!

01:37.231 --> 01:39.198
Pow, pow!

01:39.200 --> 01:41.033
Ah? Not enough?

01:41.035 --> 01:43.368
You need to feel
them guns?

01:43.370 --> 01:44.603
Verifying.

01:44.605 --> 01:48.140
Whoa!
Well, hello, frisky!

01:48.142 --> 01:49.141
[ Giggles ]

01:49.143 --> 01:52.444
Todd, I'm right here!

01:52.446 --> 01:55.380
Identifying dangerous mutant.

01:55.382 --> 01:57.616
Initiating defensive mode.

01:57.618 --> 01:59.551
[ Splashing ]

02:02.155 --> 02:03.555
Seeking human.

02:03.557 --> 02:06.391
[ Screaming ]
Human, come home to safety.

02:06.393 --> 02:07.726
Seeking human.

02:07.728 --> 02:10.696
Human,
come home to safety.

02:12.899 --> 02:15.734
Hey, Jake,
what about this one?

02:15.736 --> 02:17.669
[ Laughs ] Great.

02:17.671 --> 02:20.506
We're gonna look so great
for this funeral.

02:20.508 --> 02:22.174
How do you like
my bandeau!

02:22.176 --> 02:25.344
I was too embarrassed
to get a bra fitting.

02:25.346 --> 02:29.448
I know they are professionals,
but it's just too intimate.

02:29.450 --> 02:30.582
You look great!

02:30.584 --> 02:32.317
Ship:
Settlement detected.

02:32.319 --> 02:35.154
Continuing search
for XJ-7-7.

02:35.156 --> 02:37.756
Banana Guards: Get him!
Attack! Attack!

02:37.758 --> 02:41.527
Aaah!
Hostile cylinders
detected.

02:41.529 --> 02:44.930
Release countermeasures.
Aah!

02:44.932 --> 02:48.700
[ Muffled ] Ahh!
Hostile cylinders
immobilized.

02:50.470 --> 02:52.604
Engaging
hostile bobbleheads.

02:52.606 --> 02:55.440
[ Laser sounds ]

02:55.442 --> 02:57.009
Neutralizing.

02:57.011 --> 03:00.279
Please do not turn your system
off during neutralization.

03:02.282 --> 03:03.515
[ Crash! ]

03:03.517 --> 03:05.184
Holy mud!

03:05.186 --> 03:07.853
It took out the gumball guards
like they was nothin'!

03:07.855 --> 03:09.521
BMO doesn't like it!

03:09.523 --> 03:13.392
We gotta chop this thing
into smashaghetti.

03:13.394 --> 03:14.693
Yaaaaaaaaaa!

03:14.695 --> 03:16.828
I'll take you out
with these hug nubs!

03:16.830 --> 03:19.364
Yaaaaa!!
I'll help you, Finn!

03:19.366 --> 03:21.867
Aah! Help me, Finn!

03:21.869 --> 03:24.803
Oof!
Ship:
Hostile mutant neutralized.

03:24.805 --> 03:27.539
[ Gulps ]
<i>You got this, Finn Mertens.</i>

03:27.541 --> 03:29.408
<i>You're a buff</i>
<i>little bionic baby.</i>

03:29.410 --> 03:31.710
Rush!
Ruuuuussshhh!

03:31.712 --> 03:33.512
Rush!
Ruuuussshhh!

03:33.514 --> 03:34.513
[ Grunts ]

03:34.515 --> 03:36.148
Aaahhh!

03:36.150 --> 03:39.218
Verifying.
Human identified.

03:40.887 --> 03:43.989
Infant PG-8-7 "Mertens."

03:43.991 --> 03:47.059
[ Whoosh! ]
Aaah -- Oh.

03:47.061 --> 03:49.328
[ Whirring ]

03:49.330 --> 03:50.662
PG-8-7.

03:50.664 --> 03:52.531
Uh...you mean me?

03:52.533 --> 03:58.937
You will assist this transport
in locating seeker XJ-7-7.

03:58.939 --> 04:03.675
PG-8-7 "Mertens,"
please climb aboard.

04:03.677 --> 04:06.011
Please come aboard.
Come on.

04:06.013 --> 04:10.349
"Mertens?"
Wait, do you, like, know me?

04:10.351 --> 04:12.618
[ Smashing ]

04:14.854 --> 04:17.789
Got it! Great work
distractin' 'em, Finn!

04:17.791 --> 04:20.359
You okay, dude?

04:20.361 --> 04:22.594
I feel like that ship
might've been important.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.196
But I'm fine.

04:24.198 --> 04:27.599
Yeah, my hands are a little sore
from smashing, but I'm fine too.

04:27.601 --> 04:30.369
Eeeeeeeyaaaa!

04:30.371 --> 04:34.239
Ha! Ha! Once again
BMO comes out on top!

04:34.241 --> 04:36.141
Bzzt!
BMO!

04:36.143 --> 04:37.542
BMO, you okay?

04:37.544 --> 04:39.578
Ship: Signal received.

04:39.580 --> 04:43.548
XJ-7-7 requests transport.

04:43.550 --> 04:45.984
Both: [ Gasps ] Susan!

04:50.089 --> 04:51.089
Hey.

04:51.091 --> 04:52.324
Hi, Finn.

04:52.326 --> 04:55.394
Uh, sorry again
my grass arm busted you up.

04:55.396 --> 04:56.728
It's okay.

04:56.730 --> 04:59.831
At the time,
Susan was gonna bust <i>you</i> up.

04:59.833 --> 05:02.668
Where's Jake?
Is he okay?

05:02.670 --> 05:04.736
He's outside.
He's bringing the ship over.

05:04.738 --> 05:06.138
The ship?

05:09.509 --> 05:11.743
Oh. Ship.

05:11.745 --> 05:15.247
BMO: [ Humming ]

05:15.249 --> 05:18.250
How about it, Suze?
Does any of this look familiar?

05:18.252 --> 05:21.320
Me and Finn took this whole
bad block down ourselves!

05:21.322 --> 05:25.324
Took a bit of fanaglin', but I
never hunt what I can't catch.

05:35.268 --> 05:37.669
[ Whoosh! ]

05:37.671 --> 05:39.771
[ Drum beats ]

05:39.773 --> 05:42.607
[ Whirring ]

05:42.609 --> 05:45.210
[ Crashing ]

05:51.617 --> 05:53.518
Bubblegum:
Hey. Looking for this?

05:53.520 --> 05:56.855
I've been holding onto the
remnants of your cranial implant

05:56.857 --> 05:58.790
since you kidnapped
Finn and almost killed Jake.

05:58.792 --> 06:00.125
You remember that?

06:00.127 --> 06:03.628
I'm running a comparative
mass spec test now.

06:03.630 --> 06:05.030
[ Ding! ]
Yep.

06:05.032 --> 06:07.299
Looks like both your implant
and the ship

06:07.301 --> 06:09.634
have the same
technological origin --

06:09.636 --> 06:10.969
human technology.

06:10.971 --> 06:12.838
[ Beep ]
Finished.

06:12.840 --> 06:14.973
Looks like
BMO's finally downloaded

06:14.975 --> 06:16.541
the ship's last commands.

06:16.543 --> 06:18.076
Signal received.

06:18.078 --> 06:20.078
Proceed
to extraction point.

06:20.080 --> 06:26.151
Return Seeker XJ-7-7 and cargo
to Founders Island, home.

06:26.153 --> 06:28.153
BMO, can you give us
print outs?

06:28.155 --> 06:33.992
Yes, okay.
Printing.

06:33.994 --> 06:37.929
Hmm. Man, this island's
way far out there.

06:39.999 --> 06:42.367
Susan needs to go back here.

06:42.369 --> 06:43.769
To this island.

06:43.771 --> 06:48.573
Not sure why --
Susan having crazy week.

06:48.575 --> 06:51.343
I don't know, Susan.
It's so far.

06:51.345 --> 06:53.378
Even I don't know
what's out there.

06:53.380 --> 06:55.747
It's a pretty risky
solo mission.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.349
I'm going too.

06:57.351 --> 07:00.218
I mean, we gotta find out
where this ship came from.

07:00.220 --> 07:01.586
There could be
more of them.

07:01.588 --> 07:03.021
And if this is human-made,

07:03.023 --> 07:05.624
then there might be
other humans on that island.

07:05.626 --> 07:07.859
That'd be cool to see,
right?

07:07.861 --> 07:09.127
I'll come too!

07:09.129 --> 07:12.297
And so will we.
No, we won't.

07:12.299 --> 07:13.398
Oh.

07:13.400 --> 07:15.400
Well, it sounds like
you're all determined.

07:15.402 --> 07:17.402
You should borrow my boat,
though.

07:17.404 --> 07:18.870
This thing is trashed.

07:18.872 --> 07:20.372
We don't need a boat!

07:20.374 --> 07:23.608
Have you forgotten --
with a little imagination,

07:23.610 --> 07:28.780
I can be anything
that you could ever...

07:28.782 --> 07:29.948
Oh, I lost focus.

07:29.950 --> 07:32.284
Hey, yeah.
Can we borrow your boat?

07:35.421 --> 07:37.889
Are you up here, Fern?

07:37.891 --> 07:40.759
Hey, thanks for letting me crash
on the roof.

07:40.761 --> 07:42.160
It's nice up here.

07:42.162 --> 07:46.097
Stay as long you want!
I came up here to ask a favor.

07:46.099 --> 07:49.267
I might be gone
for a while on this trip, see,

07:49.269 --> 07:54.573
and I need someone to, uh,
cover for me here in Ooo.

07:54.575 --> 07:56.107
Are you sure?

07:56.109 --> 07:59.744
I mean, hero biz
is your whole thing,

07:59.746 --> 08:02.781
and whatever I am,
I'm not you.

08:02.783 --> 08:04.783
You can just do your own thing
with it.

08:04.785 --> 08:06.751
Like...

08:06.753 --> 08:08.487
if some huge
gross monster's

08:08.489 --> 08:10.789
gonna do murder
on a buncha innocents,

08:10.791 --> 08:12.123
uh, kill it.

08:12.125 --> 08:15.093
But kill it you-styles.
Just don't go nuts.

08:15.095 --> 08:17.929
Okay, I can handle that.

08:17.931 --> 08:19.164
Thanks for trusting me.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.433
No, thank <i>you,</i> Fern.

08:21.435 --> 08:23.235
I better go pack.

08:26.939 --> 08:30.175
We should figure out
a better thing.
Eh. Let's figure out
something better.

08:32.945 --> 08:34.379
Hey, Dad?

08:34.381 --> 08:37.048
Charlie! Hi, it's me!
It's Dad!

08:37.050 --> 08:39.985
I have to go on a sea voyage,
honey! Wanted to say bye!

08:39.987 --> 08:41.453
That's cool.

08:41.455 --> 08:43.522
Hey, you can't see this shirt,
right?

08:43.524 --> 08:46.791
This shirt has like four
different breakfasts on it.

08:46.793 --> 08:51.062
I can't hear anything!
Bye, love you! Mwah!

08:51.064 --> 08:53.231
Mmkay, Dad!
I'll tell the other pups!

08:53.233 --> 08:55.901
And I'm telling
the other pups!

09:00.406 --> 09:03.141
Aww, I'm gonna miss you
so much, lady.

09:03.143 --> 09:06.478
[ Speaking Korean ]

09:11.183 --> 09:13.385
Finn, did you bring
your nail clippers?

09:13.387 --> 09:14.753
Uh. I think so.

09:14.755 --> 09:16.821
Cool, I forgot to.

09:16.823 --> 09:19.658
Bye, treehouse!

09:19.660 --> 09:21.993
Goodbye, creator!

09:21.995 --> 09:25.430
Now me and BMO
can really "cut loose!"

09:25.432 --> 09:30.368
Look, BMO! I am pretending
to trash a hotel room!

09:30.370 --> 09:31.570
BMO?

09:36.709 --> 09:38.276
BMO: [ Softly ] Ouch.

09:38.278 --> 09:40.512
Thanks for seeing us off,
guys.

09:40.514 --> 09:43.181
Yeah, of course.
It's my boat.

09:43.183 --> 09:45.951
And we care about him,
you dingus!

09:45.953 --> 09:47.686
Come on!

09:47.688 --> 09:50.755
Sorry,
Marcy is up past her bedtime.

09:50.757 --> 09:52.357
No, it's true.

09:52.359 --> 09:55.193
I want you to be
really careful out there.

09:55.195 --> 09:56.962
Don't worry,
we've got Susan --

09:56.964 --> 09:58.563
That's not what I mean.

09:58.565 --> 10:02.033
Finn, I get the sense that this
trip's more important to you

10:02.035 --> 10:03.301
than you're letting on.

10:03.303 --> 10:05.370
I mean,
if you make it to that island,

10:05.372 --> 10:07.606
you might find out
some pretty heavy stuff.

10:07.608 --> 10:10.542
About the humans
and where you came from.

10:10.544 --> 10:12.644
About yourself.

10:12.646 --> 10:15.714
Alls I'm saying is,
you have to promise me --

10:15.716 --> 10:19.784
<i>promise</i> me --
that you'll come home safe.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.052
I...

10:21.054 --> 10:22.487
Hi, Bonnie!
Both: Ah!

10:22.489 --> 10:25.223
I'm Fern.
I kind of already know you.

10:25.225 --> 10:26.992
I have a lot
of fuzzy half-memories

10:26.994 --> 10:28.293
from when I was this guy.

10:28.295 --> 10:30.128
Well, just keep the ones
where she's our boss,

10:30.130 --> 10:31.396
and forget everything else.

10:31.398 --> 10:32.931
Susan: Finn?

10:32.933 --> 10:35.333
Hey, good morning.

10:35.335 --> 10:39.237
Boat's loaded,
ready to go.

10:42.141 --> 10:44.476
Ahh! I flinched!
It's cool.

10:44.478 --> 10:47.145
We'll be back soon,
I promise!

10:47.147 --> 10:49.481
Bye, kids!
Don't be naughty!

10:49.483 --> 10:51.950
Bubblegum:
Bye! Good luck!

10:51.952 --> 10:53.618
He'll be safe.

10:53.620 --> 10:56.955
Hey, aren't you the dude that
totaled Starchy's motorcycle?

10:56.957 --> 10:59.591
[ Waves crashing ]
